                            <comment id="151182" author="adilger" created="Thu, 5 May 2016 16:28:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been using &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6844&quot; title=&quot;replay-single test 70b failure: &amp;#39;rundbench load on * failed!&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6844&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6844&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for this failure, since the &quot;unlink&quot; vs &quot;rename&quot; operation isn&apos;t the critical part, but rather the common ENOENT error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree that this failure is far too common and needs more attention.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
